reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Gugsey Desk Organizer with File Holder Looks really nice
reviews.reviewText: Review for: Gugsey Desk Organizer with File Holder, 5-tier Paper Letter Tray File Organizer with Drawer and Pen Holder, Mesh Desktop Office Organization and Storage for School Home Office Supplies(Black) (Black) Gugsey Desk Organizer with File Holder Was easy to put together. There are directions included that are easy to understand except for one part. And that is how to attach the bottom piece. There is a thin rail/rod attached to the to the edge of the base. I wasn’t really sure if that rail was suppose to face up or face down or it was the front edge or the back edge. It was hard to tell in the diagrams. I decided to attach the base with that rod/ridge face up and in the front of the organizer. It fit and the unit is stable and even. So even if it is placed wrong I am keeping it that way. There are also 3 accessories included and are part of the completed Desk organizer. A tray which sits on the very bottom shelf. A pen holder that attaches to the rail on right side of the top shelf and a File organizer(looks like a magazine holder) is clipped onto the left side of the top shelf. There are only clips on one side of the pen holder and the file holder. The clips are attached so you cannot switch which side to put either accessory. The File holder (could also be used as a magazine or catalog holder) seemed to be taller than the 5 shelf desk organizer part. But once I put the rubber feet on the Desk organizer they made it just a little bit higher and the same height as the File holder. So now it fits like is should. Which is good because it is not that easy to detach the magazine holder from the Organizer. Actually I wasn’t able to separate the two parts at all. The Attached Pen holder is the same way The clips that attach it to the Desk organizer fit tight. I had to use a little bit of pressure to snap it into place. Both of the accessory items for my organizer are firmly attached And I doubt they will fall off if the whole unit were to fall or be moved. All of the parts of the desk organizer are metal. The shelves and the back are mesh. The sided are open, with straight metal rods that run top to bottom and side to side with a U shape the middle of the side. All of the metal is Black. The material used and the construction of the pieces look to be well made of good quality. There were not any sharp edges or burrs on the pieces. All of the screw holes lined up like they should have. Actually everything fit together evenly. I almost forgot there was also a small screwdriver included with the organizer which was nice, I didn't have to look for one that would fit the screws. The desk organizer looks really nice, It is also very sturdy and it appears to be durable. I am really happy with this desk organizer. And I would recommend it to someone who is looking for a nice desk organizer.
